#-Function--verbose.set
  Function: verbose.set
      Desc: if it's a shell terminal then turn verbose ON by default,
          : otherwise, called from another script/program, turn verbose OFF.
          : verbose.set() status is used in the ask.yn() and msg.*() commands.
          : msg.sys(), msg.die() and msg.crit() will ignore verbose status.
  Synopsis: verbose.set [[on|1] | [off|0]]
          : curstatus=$(verbose.set)
#-Function--verbose.set-------------------------------------------------------
